HEADWORD: Coxcombical
<hw>Cox*comb"ic*al</hw> <pr>(k?ks-k?m"?-k<it>a</it>l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Befitting or indicating a coxcomb; like a coxcomb;
foppish; conceited.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Cox*comb"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Studded all over in <qex>coxcombical</qex> fashion with little
brass nails.</q> <rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coxcombly</ent>⟦br⟧
